The Principal Architect / Architectural Manager is responsible for leading and managing multidisciplinary design delivery during the design phase across assigned projects. This role acts as the design-phase project lead, ensuring architectural intent, program, coordination, and deliverables across all disciplines are effectively managed in alignment with client requirements, regulatory frameworks, and CPG standards.

Key Responsibilities
- Act as the design-phase project lead, taking overall responsibility for multidisciplinary design coordination and delivery;
- Lead and manage architectural design while chairing and coordinating all design disciplines, including CS, MEP, landscape, and specialist consultants;
- Manage design cope, program, resources, and deliverables across all disciplines during the design stages;
- Serve as the primary point of contact with the Client for design-phase coordination, decisions, and submissions;
- Ensure consistent integration of architectural intent with engineering, BIM, and consultant inputs;
- Plan, monitor, and control design schedules, submissions, reviews, and approvals across disciplines;
- Identify, manage, and resolve design coordination issues, risks, and changes during the design phase;
Review and endorse key design outputs prior to Client submission to ensure quality and alignment;
- Lead and facilitate design coordination meetings, workshops, and reviews involving all disciplines;
- Ensure compliance with design standards, contractual obligations, and local regulatory requirements;
- Support mentoring, collaboration, and capability development across the multidisciplinary design team.
